Nigerian senate president, Bukola Saraki is in a closed door meeting with chairmen of 45 political parties in his office at the Senate. Saraki made this known in a tweet on his verified Twitter handle, @bukolasaraki, on Thursday, barely a day after he held a press conference addressing the siege by the state security service on members of the national assembly. “I am now meeting with the National Chairman of the 45 political parties at my office in the senate.’’ He said. 